<LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:orientation="vertical"
    tools:context="com.example.amolt.learnenglish.ReadingTab1Activity"
    android:weightSum="1">

    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent">
        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="match_parent"
            android:orientation="vertical">
            <TextView
                android:text="Success Takes Time But Surely Comes."
                android:typeface="serif"
                android:textSize="40dp"
                android:textColor="@color/colorWhite"
                android:padding="20dp"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="250dp"
                android:id="@+id/imageButton"
                android:layout_gravity="center_horizontal"
                android:background="@drawable/img7"
                android:layout_weight="0.42"
                />

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:typeface="serif"
                android:textSize="20dp"
                android:paddingTop="20dp"
                android:paddingLeft="20dp"
                android:paddingRight="20dp"
                android:text="          I was good in studies always till my 12th class. After that I joined for the chartered accountancy course. I could not clear it in my first attempt and again, not in second attempt, either.\n          One of my friends, Ashish, told me about The Secret and I searched for it and watched the documentary. Then after, I started feeling the power of my imagination and the power of attraction. It really works!\n          I noted down all my desires, goals and dreams in my diary and whenever I found time I use to go through them. I am getting them, one by one, what I wanted to have.\n          I have cleared my exam, have my guitar, and all those books that I love to read. It is magical.\n          Now I can assure myself that whatever I want, I will either have, or I will have it soon. I always lend The Secret documentary to people.\n          The simple rule is to just imagine what you want, and not what you donâ€™t want. Things will get set accordingly.\n          Thanks to Ashish for referring me to The Secret.\n          Best regards,\n          Jaya Mittal"
                />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Thank You."
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textSize="25dp"
                android:layout_gravity="center"
                android:typeface="serif"
                android:padding="10dp"
                />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Swap for Next Lesson."
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textSize="20dp"
                android:layout_gravity="center"
                android:typeface="serif"
                android:paddingBottom="10dp"
                />
        </LinearLayout>
    </ScrollView>

</LinearLayout>